= !Camping_NF
Ceres: ...

Ceres: As I thought, negotiations with Valentina are impossible. I
wish there was a way to save the resistance fighters of Jupiterino.

[Vice-Captain] Lady Ceres, the pleas for help we receive are not only
from Jupiterino.

[Vice-Captain] Valentina is a prestigious magical nation. They are not
someone we can simply deal with. Further interference in their
internal affairs would be dangerous. I believe we should only do what
we can.

Ceres: Indeed... If negotiations and protests are impossible, then
fighting is the only option left. But if we, the Knights of Messiah,
unilaterally impose our justice, then Moorduna will be seen as the
villain, especially against such a prestigious magical nation.

[Vice-Captain] Yes. Moreover, they are not an opponent we can hope to
defeat. You are aware of the rumors about Princess Lucia, aren't you,
Lady Ceres?

Ceres: Lucia is a direct descendant of the sorcerers... It's not
something to be said aloud, but.

[Vice-Captain] Yes. Therefore, Jupiterino and Valentina... are not
opponents we should engage with. It's heartbreaking to abandon the
resistance and the people, though.

Ceres: I understand... I understand very well. The strategist Hades
has told me many times. The opponent is formidable. But I have known
Luna and Lucia for a long time due to past connections.

[Vice-Captain] Lady Ceres, personal feelings must be strictly
prohibited.
Ceres: Ah. It seems this time I really can't intervene...
Ceres: ...
[Woman from the populace] Please let me see Lady Ceres!!
[Soldier] No, you can't! Don't just enter as you please!
[Soldier] I apologize. There's been a bit of a disturbance.
Ceres: What happened?

[Soldier] The people of Jupiterino have entered the camp. They're
demanding to see you, Lady Ceres.
Ceres: The people of Jupiterino...
[Soldier] It's alright. We'll drive them out immediately.

Ceres: No, let them be. I will at least listen to what they have to
say.
[Soldier] Yes...
